        <title>Installing and plotting with Julia and Gadfly.jl in Visual Code</title>
        <description>&lt;h1 id=&quot;install-julia&quot;&gt;Install julia&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;p&gt;The installation of Julia is simple. I can see main options:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ol&gt; &lt;li&gt;Standard installation&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;JuliaPro&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ol&gt; &lt;h2 id=&quot;standard-installation-of-julia&quot;&gt;Standard installation of Julia&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;Following this page https://julialang.org/downloads/platform.html, the installation is very simple.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Download https://julialang.org/downloads/index.html to your location&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Extract to /YOURPATH. Mine is /home/sergio/Downloads/julia-1.1.0&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Add Julia to PATH&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;Edit your environment&lt;/p&gt; &lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;sudo &lt;/span&gt;nano /etc/environment&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;p&gt;Add these lines:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;export &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;PATH&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$PATH&lt;/span&gt;:/home/sergio/Downloads/julia-1.1.0/bin&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;p&gt;Source your environment and type julia&lt;/p&gt; &lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;sudo source&lt;/span&gt; /etc/environment&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;h2 id=&quot;juliapro&quot;&gt;JuliaPro&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;Download the .sh file and just install it https://juliacomputing.com/products/juliapro&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Are you using Windows...</description>
